Having your [resume] in [LaTeX] has many advantages over creating it in HTML or
(god forbid) a Microsoft Word document.

## Version Control ##
Unlike having a Word Document a LaTeX based document can be placed in version
control because the source is a text document. This allows you to achieve
multiple versions of your resume by simply creating multiple branches instead of
creating different files like `resume-disqus.doc` and `resume-facebook.doc`.
Having version control also lets me be more adventurous when editing my resume
because I know I can always revert to a previous state.

## Focus on Content ##
Unlike word processing and HTML based resumes, LaTeX really lets me focus on the
content of my resume instead of the formatting. This is because it does a really
good job at preventing one or two lines of content spilling onto the next page.

